<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2293] TSSLTransportFactory.createSSLContext() leaves files open</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2293</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Even though my thrift server is shutdown and (perhaps?) GC&apos;ed, &lt;br/&gt;
the keystore file used is still locked by the VM.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In TSSLTransportFactory.createSSLContext() i see  &lt;br/&gt;
ks.load(new FileInputStream(params.keyStore), params.keyPass.toCharArray());&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The FileInputStreams are never closed, which they should.&lt;br/&gt;
Or is this done deliberately?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows 7, Java 7&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
