                            <comment id="13966637" author="terrytam" created="Fri, 11 Apr 2014 15:19:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Thanks community for finding the fix for this.  While testing and reviewing the patch, we noticed the createSSLContext() allows for the condition where both the keystore and truststore is set:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;     if (params.isKeyStoreSet &amp;amp;&amp;amp; params.isTrustStoreSet) &lt;/p&gt;
{
        ctx.init(kmf.getKeyManagers(), tmf.getTrustManagers(), null);
      }

&lt;p&gt;For the case above where both the keystore and truststore parameters are set,  the truststore file input stream should still leak (depend on GC) since it was not implicitly closed before the reference &quot;fin&quot; is reused for the keystore.  We got around this by allocating a different file input stream reference for the keystore and truststore and closed both in the finally block.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Best Regards, T.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
